That is the law of Ohio. The fact that there is a temporary injunction preventing some state officials from enforcing that law against some plaintiffs does not change the fact that Ohio law bans abortion after fetal heartbeat.
added more detail about district-court ruling enjoining the enforcement of the Arkansas abortion ban
The Texas Heartbeat Act doesn't take effect until September 1, 2021, so the legal limit in Texas is still 20 weeks until then.
Added citation of Edgar v. MITE Corp., 457 U.S. 624, 648–49 (1982) (Stevens, J., concurring)

It is not correct to say that the fetal heartbeat law was "blocked." There is currently an injunction against some state officials that temporarily prevents them from enforcing the law. But the law is still in effect, and it can be enforced by County Prosecutors outside Cuyahoga, Hamilton, Franklin, Richland, Mahoning, Montgomery, and Lucas Counties against anyone who aids or abets a post-heartbeat abortion.
